I'm a 21st ogre shammie on Tallon Zek, so good weapons to come by are harder to find and more expensive.<P>Currently, my 1hb is maxed at 88. (I use 1hb so I can use my +5 agi +35 mana totem in off hand) since I usually end up playing a support role in groups and need the mana.  If soloing I will use my Chiten shell shield.  I either use a forest giant hammer (10/35) or a vellium warhammer (don't proc yet) for stuff requiring magic to hit.  With the FG hammer, I hit for upto 22 when buffed, so I can actually tank low blues with it fairly easily.  My pierce is about 45 and is horrible to use due to low damage and frequest misses.  I'm using a normal "Spear" because that is all I can afford. heh.  The only reason I am even trying to keep the skill up in Piercing is for the epic, not that I will ever get it on PvP.  About level 14 or so I trained about 25 points into piercing and used it some.<P>But no matter what level you are you need to melee some to keep your offense and defense up.  Both of mine are withen 5 points of being maxed so they make a big difference in melee. Heck, buffed at 21st, I got better ac then my friend who is a 25th DE SK.  And I'm just wearing banded for the most part.<P>I don't know if I will ever raise my 2hb, because of the utility  of off hand items.  Plus the time involved in raising the skill.<BR>But that is just my 2 cents worth.  Sorry for dragging on.<P>Braggdor Ebonheart<BR>21st Ogre Shaman<BR>Royal Family of Thex<BR>Tallon Zek<BR>Being evil is SO good!<P>--------------------<P>Braggdor, Shaman of the Dark.  Tallon Zek.<BR>Royal Family of Thex
