My personal bugbear is my defence.  Went through 36 mainly melee soloing without it maxing.  Hit 37 and still needed a point to max. I'd suggest going to Antonica and fighting low blues for the first couple bubbles.  They hit softer and appear to give you the same chance of an increase.  So far all my weapon skills are maxed by the time I ding.  Yes 2HB is a pain to get up, but go kill Lockjaw and get the glowing wooden crook.  It's a cheezy 11/35, but it gets the skill up.  For 1 HB, if you have a friend or a high level alt, go camp the jester in Kurns for the Iksar berserker club.  7/18+fleeting fury is a fast, easy way to max out offence and 1 HB.   Still looking for a good fast piercing weapon.  But until I find one, Crystalized shadow spear wasn't too expensive.  No matter how annoying and wasteful it seems, it's always good to max those melee skills.  Being able to kinda melee has saved my groups a couple times.    <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Tanelsa Teir'dal Necro 41(semi-retired)<BR>Illessa Scaled Shaman 37<BR>Dhast The Discerning Ogress Barsher<BR>Ct the place to be
