<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
All weapon skills are a pain to raise for non-melee types , I suggest that around lvl 20 goto the single avaik spawn in Lake Rathe and  use your best slow and disempower, but keep him rooted so you can step back and heal yourself.  I know this is boring but stay there for a few lvls until your main weapon skill is mastered(piercing is now 110 for me) and your others are at least 50.  This spwan ranges from 16-20 in lvls so they give xp until 26 and will raise your weapons skills.  <P>Dueling a PC does not cause any skills to raise , I tried it and unless something has changed in 6 months, its a waist of time.<P>Another spot a friend told me about was the names orc in SRO, Ortallius.  He is a lvl 30 pali that will be blue until almost lvl45.  He is not supposed to hit that hard and only double attacks no dual wield and never has a weapon.  But remember he has Temple of Ro faction and a friend nearby so don't kill him and pull him close to the sro/oasis zone.<P>PS our weapon skills are set to be <BR>level X 4 for a max per level.<BR>After a weapon skill is mastered i.e. reaches 100 you can't train in it no more even if you have the points and money.<BR>There are 2HB's out there that have better damage/delay ratios than our Epic so work for it, I like piercing and 2HB.<P><BR>Good luck <BR>Kylyn Level 26 Shaman of Justice on Quellious soon to xfer to Karana
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
